# Frontend Project Overview

## Project Structure
This is a modern Next.js 15 frontend application built with TypeScript and Tailwind CSS:

### Core Technologies
- **Next.js 15**: React framework with App Router and Turbo mode
- **React 19**: Latest React with modern features
- **TypeScript 5.8**: Strict type checking and modern syntax
- **Tailwind CSS 4.0**: Utility-first CSS framework with CSS variables
- **Zod**: Runtime type validation and schema definition

### Project Architecture
- **App Router**: Uses Next.js 13+ App Router pattern
- **Type Safety**: Full TypeScript coverage with strict configuration
- **Environment Validation**: T3 Env for type-safe environment variables
- **Package Manager**: PNPM for fast, efficient dependency management

### Key Directories
- **Entry Point**: [src/app/page.tsx](mdc:src/app/page.tsx) - Main homepage
- **Layout**: [src/app/layout.tsx](mdc:src/app/layout.tsx) - Root layout with metadata
- **Environment**: [src/env.js](mdc:src/env.js) - Type-safe environment configuration
- **Styles**: [src/styles/globals.css](mdc:src/styles/globals.css) - Global CSS and Tailwind imports
- **Configuration**: [tsconfig.json](mdc:tsconfig.json) - TypeScript configuration

### Development Tools
- **ESLint**: Next.js + TypeScript ESLint configuration
- **Prettier**: Code formatting with Tailwind CSS plugin
- **Type Checking**: Strict TypeScript compilation
- **Linting**: ESLint with Next.js and TypeScript rules

## Architecture Principles
- **Type Safety First**: Comprehensive TypeScript coverage
- **Modern React**: Use latest React 19 features and patterns
- **Performance**: Next.js Turbo mode and optimizations
- **Accessibility**: Built-in Next.js accessibility features
- **SEO**: Metadata API and server-side rendering
